uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs

Class RadioButtonInput<V,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.RadioButtonInput<V,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - type of value
    T - type of item
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Input<V>, ItemInput<T>, ListInput<V,T>, ParseInput<V>

    public class RadioButtonInput<V,T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ListInput<V,T>, ParseInput<V>
    Wrapper class to convert a ListInput to be displayed as a RadioButton. The input is assumed not to be optional. Note that this class implements ParseInput. If the nested input does not also implement this interface then the convert(Object) method needs to be able to convert the String representation of the value.
    Author:
    spb
